Dear Axiom User:

I have just completed updating the axiom-developer.org
web site to include some of the new features that have
been under test: 1) You can now use both Axiom and Reduce
on these interactive web pages. 2) The Axiom portal
now includes an extensive bibliography of publications
on Axiom and on Reduce in the "References" section.

Click http://page.axiom-developer.org/zope/mathaction
to access the MathAction wiki web site.

Click http://page.axiom-developer.org/zope/Plone
to access the Axiom/Reduce Portal.

Finally, you can also continue to help with testing and
the development at http://test.axiom-developer.org currently
I am workin on the multilingual user interface, noweb-style
"literate programming" features for creating wiki pages,
and generation of graphical output. 

Regards to all.

Bill Page.



